FBIS4-28188 "dreas110_c_94011" FBIS-EAS-94-110 Daily Report 5 Jun 1994 North Korea KCNA: ROK Workers Demand Higher Pay KCNA: ROK Workers Demand Higher Pay SK0506085694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0805 GMT 5 Jun 94 SK0506085694 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- About 2,000 workers affiliated with the subway trade union council held a rally in the Chongmyo Park in Seoul on June 2 and vowed to win in the wage-hike struggle for 1994, a Seoul-based radio reported. Pointing to the instability of working conditions, the workers at the rally called for the enforcement of an 8-hour workday. They rejected the wage hike draft agreed upon between the subsidized South Korean General Federation of Trade Unions (Nochong) and the general federation of managers councils and demanded a wage hike up to a level sufficient to ensure living.
